import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_counts = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = job_counts.plot.bar(x='job', y='count', legend=False)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of job categories in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Job Categories")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 'female']
    
    plt.plot(female_data['year'], female_data['perc'], label='Female', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage')
    plt.title('How has the percentage of females in the dataset changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='job', columns='sex', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))

    plt.title("What is the gender distribution in each job category?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Job Category")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.legend(title="Sex")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    total_count = data['count'].sum()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axhline(y=total_count, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Total Count: {total_count:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the total count of individuals in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks([])  # Hide x-axis labels
    plt.yticks([])  # Hide y-axis labels
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_perc = data.groupby('job')['perc'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.pie(job_perc['perc'], labels=job_perc['job'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job categories in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(job_perc['job'], loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
